File: Springbok captain Siya Kolisi has promised to give back to his community of Zwide in Port Elizabeth and inspire the youth. JOHANNESBURG - Things just keep getting better for Springbok skipper Siya Kolisi. Kolisi has been nominated for the BBC World Sports Star of the Year award. READ: Kolisi thanks Erasmus for believing in him He is up against Tiger Woods, runner Eliud Kipchoge, and former Australian Cricket captain, Steve Smith among others. Kolisi has been gracious on his nomination, tweeting that the world cup win was not just about him, but a team effort. After lifting the Webb Ellis Cup in Japan last month, Kolisi has been enjoying recognition for being the first black captain to win the rugby world cup.